content: Note for new student: When performing participation check, the button at the bottom labeled "I am here" will be enabled, please click it in 20 seconds
We now begin our second lesson of Tactics.
Today we will learn what is Positional Style and how to use it, and, how to find out best Positional moves.

There is no word in English that would describe the method that we learn today,
therefore I named it myself as Positional Style.
means development instead of direct attack?
when you make a move to use later
a method to get a good position for future attacks?
control game...) if you play as black you try to get white's good points and become stronger and stronger)
to cover a part of the board
wow, all answers so different, yet, somewhat correct.
Let me try to define it.. as I see it.
Positional Style is the method that focuses on total domination and safety,
safety is more important than win
sometimes, safety helps to win more than other styles
no need to keep tempo, for some situations
If you can control the whole board, and you have good structures and key points, and you have eliminated all opponents chances to develop, then your positional style succeeded 100%.
Usually, a mastered Positional Style ends with win.
But to do so...) needs a good player
Please note that Positional Style is the tool of black stones player.
In the next lessons we will learn what is white's Style.
If white has so good position which allows white to dominate and use Positional Style,
then in fact white would not need it,
because as white has the grea advantage of forbidden moves,
white could win sooner without Positional Style.
But black has the chance to go first..
the standard game goes like this:
white defends and attempts to break control
while you defend, you cannot use positional style
and once you get control as white, you will win soon,
Positional Style is not suitable for every player.
There are players who never use it.
For example, Shigeru Nakamura never uses Positional style.
may we see the style in an example?
In the future classes, we will learn about Straight Style techniques as well.
I am sorry. I will behave.

If you are good at Positional Style, you can forget 50% of all theory, and you still win all the games.
or variants that are not often used,
and those variants require precise Straight Style,.

and most of you know black win here.

to put these two 5th moves or not.

Black wins thanks to the source for direct Style

By placing this 5th move, which is actually very powerful, but hard to find,
I relieve myself from all the pressure of required Straight Style.
here black controls the whole position.
Black has no hurry to win,
and one can develop step by step until wins.
But, as you see, active defense is out of question,
and any passive move allows black to continue slow development,
black can often use more than one way of development
And black is playing without any fear or pressure
But if you play theoretical 5th move,
you are under the pressure of mixing up direct attack
We will not focus on detailed analysis of i7, its not important.
Important is to notice the power of Positional Style
but sometimes it's hard to find best position
A good player can 100% win with 5-i10
But weaker player can win by g9 more0
